  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-04 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. Model Risk Level 3. Thirteen credibility factors are addressed; twelve are fully assessed and one — Equivalency of input parameters — carries factorStatus 'not-assessed' on the grounds that the modelling team argued the factor does not apply because boundary conditions were taken directly from device specifications. This rationale conflates inapplicability with non-assessment: the factor is simply left unscored rather than formally scoped out. At MRL 3 the absence of an assessed equivalency-of-inputs evaluation materially weakens the credibility argument, triggering W-EP-04.",
