      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver version controlled; regression test suite executed; all relevant CFD modules verified against known analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under a validated software QA plan. Version locked in the simulation archive. Regression tests covering rotating-frame and species-transport modules passed without deviation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests performed on canonical rotating-channel flow; observed order matches theoretical order within 10%.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy verification performed on a 2-D rotating channel analogue. Observed spatial order was 1.87 against a theoretical 2.0 — within tolerance for the discretisation scheme employed. Temporal order was not separately verified for the steady-state RANS solution."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% on primary QoI (hemolysis index) at the operating point of maximum shear stress.",
      "rationale": "Three-level Richardson extrapolation performed on a 4M, 8M, and 16M cell sequence. GCI on hemolysis index was 3.2% at the peak-shear operating point, satisfying the 5% threshold. Wall y+ maintained below 1 on all blood-contacting surfaces."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and traceable; fluid temperature, viscosity, and hematocrit controlled within ±5% of target.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark test conditions were used. Temperature and viscosity were controlled; hematocrit was held at 35±2%. However, the inlet turbulence intensity was not independently measured during the bench test, introducing a minor uncontrolled source of variability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalised RMS error on hemolysis index < 15% across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Normalised RMS error across five operating points was 18.4%, exceeding the 15% acceptance criterion. The largest deviation occurred at the low-flow, high-speed condition where secondary recirculation zones were under-predicted by the k-omega SST turbulence model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (hemolysis index) directly maps to clinical endpoint; power-law hemolysis model parameters calibrated to human red blood cells.",
      "rationale": "The modified power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model uses HI as the primary output, which maps directly to the clinical acceptance threshold. Model constants were calibrated to human RBC fragility data from Heuser & Opitz (1980) and confirmed against Zhang et al. (2011)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on geometry and operating conditions within 20% of COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic pump geometry, which shares the same impeller class as the target VAD but differs in volute design. Operating conditions span the COU envelope but the highest-speed point (3500 RPM) was not included in the validation dataset, leaving a gap at the upper boundary of the COU."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residuals converge to < 1e-6 for continuity and momentum; energy imbalance < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to continuity residuals below 1e-7 and momentum residuals below 5e-8. Global energy imbalance was 0.04%. Double-precision arithmetic used throughout to suppress round-off accumulation in the hemolysis scalar transport equation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent technical review of simulation setup completed; checklist-based boundary condition verification documented.",
      "rationale": "An independent CFD engineer reviewed the simulation setup against the team's internal checklist. Two minor discrepancies in rotating-frame reference specification were identified and corrected prior to production runs. Final setup signed off by the lead analyst."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by sensitivity study; hemolysis constitutive model validated against independent dataset.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST selected after a three-model sensitivity study (k-eps realizable, k-omega SST, SST-SAS). SST produced the lowest RMS error on PIV velocity fields. Hemolysis model was validated against Heuser & Opitz data but not against a fully independent clinical dataset, leaving residual model-form uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and operating boundary conditions characterised with documented uncertainty; Monte Carlo propagation performed.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity (Carreau model), density, and hemolysis model exponents characterised with ±1-sigma bounds. Monte Carlo UQ (n=500) propagated input uncertainty through to hemolysis index. 95th-percentile HI remained below the clinical threshold at four of five operating points."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Pump geometry manufactured to within drawing tolerances; surface roughness measured and within specification.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump test article manufactured by Delphi Flow Technologies. CMM verification confirmed impeller blade angles within ±0.3°. Surface roughness Ra measured at 0.8 µm on blood-contacting surfaces, consistent with the CFD smooth-wall assumption."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal equivalency mapping between validation experiment input parameters and COU input parameters documented and scored.",
      "rationale": "The modelling team concluded that this factor does not apply to the present COU because boundary conditions were taken directly from device-level specifications with no intermediate experimental characterisation step, and therefore no equivalency mapping was considered necessary. However, no formal scoping-out analysis was performed and the factor was not scored against the MRL-3 required level. The factor is consequently carried as not-assessed rather than not-applicable, leaving an unquantified epistemic gap in the credibility argument at a model risk level where all thirteen factors require substantive evidence."
    }
