    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the simulation evidence package on the basis that twelve of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed, that Monte Carlo UQ was completed, and that the overall hemolysis predictions remained below the clinical threshold at the nominal operating points. The unassessed Equivalency of input parameters factor was noted as a gap but was not treated as a blocking issue because the team considered it inapplicable. This reasoning is the target weakness: at MRL 3 the factor's absence materially weakens the credibility argument and the correct encoding would be 'not-applicable' with a documented justification, not 'not-assessed' with an informal verbal dismissal.",
